ican drummer and composer\n*  1965   &ndash; [[Maninder Singh (cricketer)|Maninder Singh]], Indian cricketer\n*[[1966]] &ndash; [[Henry Bond]], English photographer and curator\n*  1966   &ndash; [[Grigori Perelman]], Russian mathematician\n*  1966   &ndash; [[Naoki Hattori]], Japanese race car driver\n*[[1967]] &ndash; [[Ta\u015fk\u0131n Aksoy]], German-Turkish footballer and manager\n*[[1968]] &ndash; [[Fabio Baldato]], Italian cyclist\n*  1968   &ndash; [[Peter DeBoer]], Canadian ice hockey player and coach\n*  1968   &ndash; [[Darren Dreger]], Canadian sportscaster\n*  1968   &ndash; [[David Gray (musician)|David Gray]], English-Welsh singer-songwriter, guitarist, and producer\n*  1968   &ndash; [[Tim Leveque]], Canadian ice hockey player\n*  1968   &ndash; [[Denise Pearson]], English singer-songwriter \n*  1968   &ndash; [[Marcel Theroux]], Ugandan-English journalist and author\n*[[1969]] &ndash; [[Cayetana Guill\u00e9n Cuervo]], Spanish actress, director, and screenwriter\n*  1969   &ndash; [[Virginie Despentes]], French author, screenwriter, and director\n*  1969   &ndash; [[Laura Kightlinger]], American actress, comedian, producer, and screenwriter\n*  1969   &ndash; [[Svetlana Krivelyova]], Russian shot putter\n*  1969   &ndash; [[S\u00f8ren Rasted]], Danish singer-songwriter, guitarist, and producer\n*[[1970]] &ndash; [[Rivers Cuomo]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist \n*[[1970]] &ndash; [[Chris Cairns]], New Zealand cricketer\n*[[1971]] &ndash; [[N\u00f3ra K\u00f6ves]], Hungarian tennis player\n*[[1972]] &ndash; [[Natalie MacMaster]], Canadian fiddler\n*  1972   &ndash; [[Marek Jerzy Minakowski]], Polish philosopher, historian, genealogist\n*[[1973]] &ndash; [[Sam Adams (American football)|Sam Adams]], American football player\n*  1973   &ndash; [[Tanner Foust]], American race car driver and television host\n*  1973   &ndash; [[Mattias Hellberg]], Swedish singer-songwriter \n*  1973   &ndash; [[Stuart Karppinen]], Australian cricketer and coach\n*  1973   &ndash; [[Ville Laihiala]], Finnish singer-songwriter and guitarist \n*[[1974]] &ndash; [[Valeri Bure]], Russian-American ice hockey player\n*[[1975]] &ndash; [[Ante Covic]], Australian footballer\n*  1975   &ndash; [[Jeff Davis (writer)|Jeff Davis]], American screenwriter and producer\n*  1975   &ndash; [[Jennifer Nicole Lee]], American model, actress, and author\n*  1975   &ndash; [[Jaan Pehk]], Estonian singer-songwriter and guitarist \n*  1975   &ndash; [[Riccardo Scimeca]], English footballer\n*[[1976]] &ndash; [[Kym Marsh]], English singer-songwriter and actress \n*[[1977]] &ndash; [[Romain Mesnil]], French pole vaulter\n*  1977   &ndash; [[Earthwind Moreland]], American football player\n*[[1978]] &ndash; [[Ethan Embry]], American actor\n*[[1979]] &ndash; [[Esther Anderson (Australian actress)|Esther Anderson]], Australian actress\n*  1979   &ndash; [[Nila H\u00e5kedal]], Norwegian volleyball player\n*  1979   &ndash; [[Miguel Pate]], American long jumper\n*  1979   &ndash; [[Ryan Pickett (filmmaker)|Ryan Pickett]], American director, producer, and screenwriter\n*[[1980]] &ndash; [[Florent Malouda]], French footballer\n*  1980   &ndash; [[Diego Mendieta]], Paraguayan footballer (d. 2012)\n*  1980   &ndash; [[Jamario Moon]], American basketball player\n*  1980   &ndash; [[Juan Carlos Navarro (basketball)|Juan Carlos Navarro]], Spanish basketball player\n*  1980   &ndash; [[Darius Vassell]], English footballer\n*  1980   &ndash; [[Markus Winkelhock]], German racing driver\n*[[1981]] &ndash; [[Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans]], American actor and producer\n*  1981   &ndash; [[Blake Judd (filmmaker)|Blake Judd]], American actor, director, and producer\n*  1981   &ndash; [[David Madden (Jeopardy! contestant)|David Madden]], founder and executive director of both the [[National History Bee]] and the [[National History Bowl]] who was a 19-day champion on ''[[Jeopardy!]]''.\n*  1981   &ndash; [[Radim Vrbata]], Czech ice hockey player\n*[[1982]] &ndash; [[Kene