be Live]]\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|-\n|August 7\n|rowspan=2| [[Boston, Massachusetts|Boston]]\n|rowspan=2| [[Fenway Park]]\n|rowspan=2|\u2014 \n|rowspan=2|\u2014\n|-\n|August 8\n|-\n!colspan=4| Total\n!\u2014\n!\u2014\n|-\n|}\n\n==Musicians==\n*[[Bob Weir]] \u2013 guitar, vocals\n*[[Mickey Hart]] \u2013 drums\n*[[Bill Kreutzmann]] \u2013 drums\n*[[John Mayer]] \u2013 guitar, vocals\n*[[Oteil Burbridge]] \u2013 bass, percussion, vocals\n*[[Jeff Chimenti]] \u2013 keyboards, vocals\n\n==See also==\n* [[Reunions of the Grateful Dead]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Grateful Dead}}\n\n[[Category:2020 concert tours]]\n[[Category:Grateful Dead]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox concert\n|concert_tour_name = Summer Tour 2020\n| type = tour\n| image = Dead-and-Company-Summer-Tour-2020.jpg\n| image_size = 250px\n| alt = \n| artist = [[Dead & Company]]\n| location= United States\n| gross= \n| album= \n| start_date = {{Start date|2020|07|10}}\n| end_date = {{End date|2020|08|08}}\n| number_of_legs = 1 (planned)\n| number_of_shows = 17 (planned)\n| last_tour = [[Dead & Company Fall Fun Run 2019]]\n| this_tour = '''Dead & Company Summer Tour 2020'''\n| next_tour = \n}}\n\n'''Dead & Company Summer Tour 2020''' is an upcoming concert tour by the rock band [[Dead & Company]]. It was supposed to be the continuation of the group's Summer Tour series and a followup to their [[Dead & Company Summer Tour 2019|2019 Tour]]. The tour comprised 17 dates at 14 locations from July 10 to August 8, 2020. It was cancelled on April 21, 2020 as a response to the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dead & Company Details Summer Tour 2020|url=https://www.jambase.com/article/dead-company-summer-tour-2020|first=Scott|last=Bernstein|date=February 6, 2020|accessdate=February 6, 2020|website=JamBase}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first= Angie |last=Martoccio |date=February 6, 2020 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dead-and-company-summer-tour-948643/ |title=Dead & Company Map Summer Tour Dates |website=Rolling Stone |access-date=February 7, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Gil |last=Kaufman |date=February 6, 2020 |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/touring/8550304/dead-company-tour-dates |title=Dead & Company Line Up Summer 2020 Tour: See the Dates |website=Billboard |access-date=February 7, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=<!-- staff, no byline--> |date=February 6, 2020 |url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/dead-company-summer-2020-tour-dates-1203495106/ |title=Dead & Company Reveal Summer 2020 Tour Dates |website=Variety |access-date=February 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Tour dates== \n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:12em;\"| Date<ref name=\"Official-1\">{{cite web | url=http://deadandcompany.com/ | title=Dead & Company | publisher=Dead & Company | accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\"| City\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Country\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Venue\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Attendance\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Revenue\n|-\n!colspan=6|North America\n|-\n|July 10, 2020\n|rowspan=2| [[Boulder, Colorado|Boulder]]\n|rowspan=17|United States\n|rowspan=2| [[Folsom Field]]\n|rowspan=2|\u2014 \n|rowspan=2|\u2014\n|-\n|July 11\n|-\n|July 13\n|[[Maryland Heights, Missouri|Maryland Heights]]\n|[[Hollywood Casino Amphitheatre (Maryland Heights, Missouri)|Hollywood Casino Amphitheater]]\n|\u2014 \n|\u2014\n|-\n|July 15\n|[[Noblesville, Indiana|Noblesville]]\n|[[Ruoff Music Center]]\n|\u2014 \n|\u2014\n|-\n|July 17\n|[[Atlanta, Georgia|Atlanta]]\n|[[Truist Park]]\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|-\n|July 18\n|[[Raleigh, North Carolina|Raleigh]]\n|[[Coastal Credit Union Music Park]]\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|-\n|July 20\n|[[Cincinnati, Ohio|Cincinnati]]\n|[[Riverbend Music Center]]\n|\u2014 \n|\u2014\n|-\n|July 22\n|[[Clarkston, Michigan|Clarkston]]\n|[[DTE Energy Music Theatre]]\n|\u2014 \n|\u2014\n|-\n|July 24\n|rowspa