l.de/international/germany/spiegel-cover-story-how-silicon-valley-shapes-our-future-a-1021557.html |newspaper=Der Spiegel}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Sturgeon |first=Timothy J. |date=December 2000 |title=Chapter Two: How Silicon Valley Came to Be |url=https://ipc.mit.edu/sites/default/files/documents/00-014.pdf |journal=Industrial Performance Center |publisher=Massachusetts Institute of Technology}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Williams |first=James C. |date=December 2013 |title=From White Gold to Silicon Chips: Hydraulic Technology, Electric Power and Silicon Valley |type=Abstract |journal=Social Science Information |publisher=[[Sage Publications]] |volume=52 |issue=4 |pages=558\u2013574|doi=10.1177/0539018413497834 }} (Subscription required for full text.)\n\n===Audiovisual===\n*  {{cite AV media|year=2012 |others=Narrated by Leonard Nimoy. |title=Silicon Valley: A Five Part Series |url=http://www.siliconvalleyhistorical.org/silicon-valley-series-film/ |medium=DVD|publisher=Silicon Valley Historical Association}}\n* {{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=August 27, 2010 |title=A Weekend in Silicon Valley |url=https://www.nytimes.com/slideshow/2010/08/27/travel/20100905SILICON.html |type=Slideshow |newspaper=The New York Times }}\n* {{cite AV media|year=2012 |others=Narrated by Leonard Nimoy. |title=Silicon Valley: A Five Part Series |url=http://www.siliconvalleyhistorical.org/silicon-valley-series-film/ |medium=DVD|publisher=Silicon Valley Historical Association}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wikivoyage}}\n* [http://www.nps.gov/nr/travel/santaclara/ Santa Clara County: California's Historic Silicon Valley]\u2014A [[National Park Service]] website\n* [https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/americanexperience/films/silicon/ Silicon Valley]\u2014An [[American Experience]] documentary broadcast in 2013\n* {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071220023204/http://www2.sjsu.edu/depts/anthropology/svcp/ |date=December 20, 2007 |title=Silicon Valley 